{"comments":"Reflection Symmetry — Mirror axes for bilateral symmetry.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nA reflection axis defines a line across which a shape can be mirrored.\nThe axis is characterized by its angle from horizontal:\n- 0° = horizontal axis (reflects top-bottom)\n- 90° = vertical axis (reflects left-right)\n- 45° = diagonal axis\n- 135° = anti-diagonal axis\n\n## Use Cases\n\n- UI layouts with bilateral symmetry\n- Logo and icon design\n- Mirror transformations\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show)\n- Geometry.Angle (Degrees)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["angle",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Angle"],"Degrees"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[75,61],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Reflection.purs","start":[75,24]},"title":"ReflectionAxis"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Symmetry","Reflection"],"ReflectionAxis"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[77,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Reflection.purs","start":[77,1]},"title":"eqReflectionAxis"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Symmetry","Reflection"],"ReflectionAxis"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[78,56],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/